verb.description: To make a humming, buzzing, or droning sound; to move with, or as if with, such a sound; to move quickly. Also occasionally with object: to cause to move with such a sound; to propel quickly.

exclamation.description: Representing a buzzing, humming, or droning sound.

origin: Late 19th century; earliest use found in Notes and Queries. Imitative<br>mid 19th century; earliest use found in Once a Week: an illustrated miscellany of literature, art, science, and popular information. Imitative.
